Senator Ibrahim Mohammed Bomai representing Yobe South senatorial district has in a new year message assured constituents of improved service delivery, legislation and empowerment. According to him “as we start witnessing the year 2022, we are more committed towards bringing additional people’s oriented programmes and projects for the progress and development of our people of Yobe South.We are highly indebted to the good people of Yobe South for recognizing our efforts and appreciating our modest achievements despite the limitations of finances”. “I wish His Excellency Hon Mai Mala Buni, the Executive Governor of Yobe State, the Deputy Governor His Excellency Idi Barde Gubana, His Excellency Distinguished Senator Alhaji Ibrahim Geidam, Right Honourable Ahmed Lawan Mirwa the Speaker Yobe State House of Assembly and other Legislators, the Chief Judge of the State and other Lordships, Our Royal Fathers, Our State Chairman of the APC Alhaji Mohammed Gadaka and other Members of the State Exco of our great Party, the APC, other APC stakeholders, Women, Youths, all the people of Yobe South and our dear State a very happy and prosperous new year”. Idimogu Fetes Oshodi/Isolo Constituents At Christmas Lawmaker Distributes Food Items To Constituents “I pray that the Almighty Allah will continue to sustain peace and unity in Yobe South and in our State, as we begin our journey through the course of the year 2022”.